{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "PA Plan Advisor API",
    "description": "## Before you call the API\n\n1. **Collection → Authorization → Type: No Auth.** Do **not** use the collection **API Key** or **Bearer** tabs — they conflict with per-request headers and leave Bearer empty.\n2. Create a **Postman Environment** and add **`pa_plan_api_key`** (same as Railway `PA_PLAN_API_KEY`).\n3. Run **folder `0. Supabase — login`** first: set **`supabase_url`**, **`supabase_anon_key`**, **`supabase_email`**, **`supabase_password`** in the environment. The **Tests** script saves **`access_token`** for you.\n4. Select that environment (top-right), then call `/api/...` requests.\n\nEach API request sends **`X-API-Key: {{pa_plan_api_key}}`** and **`Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}`** as normal headers.\n\nSee docs/API-USER-ENDPOINTS.md.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "https://planadvisor-dev.up.railway.app"
    },
    {
      "key": "profile_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "scenario_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "user_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "rule_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "plan_id",
      "value": ""
